author: acerojano
title: Miss Netherlands shows gratitude after her Beyonce moves went viral
text:
INQUIRER.net / 10:47 PM January 31, 2017 
After her Beyonce moves went viral, Miss Netherlands Zoey Ivory on Monday expressed her gratitude on Instagram. 
“Thanks everyone for all the sweet messages and love I’m still getting! The girl with the natural curls and tattoos who does crazy dances to “Single Ladies” unfortunately didn’t make it to the Top 13 of Miss Universe. But I’ll make the top of something else that comes on my path. This was not my destiny, but an experience I can add to my journey!” she wrote. 
At the rehearsals for the 65th Miss Universe pageant last January 26, as the candidates were all lined up in their evening gowns, Miss Netherlands was seen dancing to Beyonce’s “Single Ladies,” lightening up the atmosphere. ADVERTISEMENT 
“My time in the Philippines was indescribable and I will find it hard to leave you all! I didn’t win the crown, but I hope that I’ve won your hearts. Thanks everyone, keep loving yourself AND SEE YOU AT THE AFTERPARTYYYY” Ivory added. 
As of writing, her video has garnered 19M views.
